# Cloudflare Pages headers. Two concerns:
#   1. A global baseline of security headers (the /* block).
#   2. Freshness for the service worker + manifest so updates propagate fast.

# Baseline security headers for every response (defense-in-depth).
# All NON-resource-restricting: none of these can break the same-origin
# ONNX/WASM/worker pipeline or the catalog's product images. A full resource
# CSP (script-src / img-src / connect-src / worker-src) is deliberately NOT set
# here — it needs live verification against onnxruntime-web (needs
# wasm-unsafe-eval), the module workers, and external image hosts before it can
# be enforced without breaking the app. `frame-ancestors 'self'` (below) is the
# one CSP directive that is safe to ship now: it restricts framing only, never
# resource loading.
/*
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin
  X-Frame-Options: SAMEORIGIN
  Content-Security-Policy: frame-ancestors 'self'
  Cross-Origin-Opener-Policy: same-origin
  Permissions-Policy: accelerometer=(), autoplay=(), camera=(), display-capture=(), geolocation=(), gyroscope=(), magnetometer=(), microphone=(), midi=(), payment=(), usb=()

# Keep the service worker and manifest fresh so updates propagate immediately.
/sw.js
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=0, must-revalidate
/manifest.webmanifest
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=0, must-revalidate
